  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate the effects of omega-3 fatty acid supplementation on inflammation in
      trauma patients. The main hypothesis is that such supplementation will reduce the presence of
      biomarkers of systemic inflammation, as compared to placebo
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This prospective, randomized study will evaluate the effects of omega-3 fatty acid
      supplementation on inflammatory response in multi-injured trauma patients. Its primary
      objective is to compare the intensity of inflammation between an active omega-3 group and a
      placebo group.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
